y been edited and is awaiting review.     David Rutley       Share       As always, the hon. Gentleman asks an insightful question. Our regulatory regime currently lets local residents have their say on two stages in the environmental permitting process: when the application is received by the Environment Agency; and at the draft decision stage, before the permit is finalised. A public consultation takes place once the planning application has been permitted. On 17 May, the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy and the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government set out that they would be strengthening community engagement further by consulting in due course on the potential to make pre-application consultation a statutory requirement.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Mr Dennis Skinner (Bolsover) (Lab)       Share       Why does the Minister not make a statement on behalf of the Government to stop fracking altogether?     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     David Rutley       Share       The Government believe, rightly, that shale gas plays an important part in our energy mix and will be an important bridging fuel in the transition to renewable technologies.     Share         Leaving the EU: Fishing Industry                The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Jim Shannon (Strangford) (DUP)       Share       8. What steps he is taking to support the UK fishing industry as the UK leaves the EU.  [905714]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Mini